Prior to orally requesting a contribution or when requesting a contribution in writing, a professional solicitor shall clearly disclose:
The professional solicitor's name, as set out in the registration statement filed with the Attorney General pursuant to KRS 367.652, phone number or e-mail address, and the fact that the professional solicitor is being paid for providing services;
The name of the charitable organization the professional solicitor represents and a description of how the contributions raised by the solicitation will be used for a charitable or civic purpose; and
If the professional solicitor places or maintains a receptacle in public view for the purpose of collecting contributions in the form of clothing, household items, and other items, the receptacle shall contain a sign or label that:
Includes the information contained in paragraphs (a) and (b) of this subsection;
Includes a statement that reads as follows: "Items donated here support, in part, a for-profit professional solicitor.";
Is in lettering not less than three (3) inches in height and one-half (1/2) inch in width; and
Is placed immediately below the opening in the receptacle used to deposit donations.
